      "why_choose_us": "Mountain Spine & Orthopedics uses a combination of physical examination, high resolution imaging (MRI or CT), and diagnostic medial branch nerve blocks to confirm facet joints as the source of pain.",
      "recovery_info": "Under Xray guidance, a small probe is placed near the medial branch nerves, and radiofrequency energy is used to heat and deactivate them. The entire procedure takes about 30 minutes per level and is performed under light sedation or local anesthesia. Patients typically resume normal activity within a day or two.",
      "benefits": "Pain relief may begin within days and often lasts six months to over a year. The nerves can regenerate over time, and repeat treatments may be performed if symptoms return.",
