      "conditions_treated": "Facet joint arthritis, spinal osteoarthritis, chronic mechanical back or neck pain, whiplash injuries, and degenerative changes that lead to joint instability or persistent inflammation.",
      "why_choose_us": "Mountain Spine & Orthopedics performs a full physical examination, imaging (MRI, CT), and diagnostic medial branch blocks to confirm the source of pain and determine the most appropriate treatment path.",
      "recovery_info": "Facet blocks are used for both diagnosis and temporary relief. Rhizotomy uses radiofrequency energy to ablate nerves transmitting pain. If symptoms return or instability is found, facet fusion may be performed through a minimally invasive approach using bone grafts to fuse the joint and reduce motion related pain. Recovery timelines vary by procedure but typically involve minimal downtime and progressive rehabilitation.",
